<br>
I've always believed that the Dark Elves learned it through their own dealings and experimentations.  I know that the Iksar learned all of the Arcane magics from old Shissar texts (Yes, they know Magery, Enchantry and Wizardry-those are just considered heretical arts by the Empire, and so are only practiced by the forsaken or in secret).  But the Tier'Dal, Trolls, Ogres, and Humans could just as easily have stumbled across it as they did the other schools of magic. <p><center><b>Kelisk Mae'Lokh</b></center><br><center>Chancellor of Skathris Ven'Sho--Patriarch of Cabilis</center><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=355953"><i>Inspect Kelisk?</i></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.0.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href=http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html>JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

